  <text>
    <status value="extensions"/><div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><p>This value set includes codes based on the following rules:</p><ul><li>Include these codes as defined in <a href="http://terminology.hl7.org/5.3.0/CodeSystem-v3-ActCode.html"><code>http://terminology.hl7.org/CodeSystem/v3-ActCode</code></a><table class="none"><tr><td style="white-space:nowrap"><b>Code</b></td><td><b>Display</b></td><td><b>Definition</b></td><td><b><a href="ConceptMap-CMVFencounterClass.html">VF_encounterClass</a></b></td></tr><tr><td><a href="http://terminology.hl7.org/5.3.0/CodeSystem-v3-ActCode.html#v3-ActCode-IMP">IMP</a></td><td>inpatient encounter</td><td>A patient encounter where a patient is admitted by a hospital or equivalent facility, assigned to a location where patients generally stay at least overnight and provided with room, board, and continuous nursing service.</td><td/></tr><tr><td><a href="http://terminology.hl7.org/5.3.0/CodeSystem-v3-ActCode.html#v3-ActCode-AMB">AMB</a></td><td>ambulatory</td><td>A comprehensive term for health care provided in a healthcare facility (e.g. a practitioneraTMs office, clinic setting, or hospital) on a nonresident basis. The term ambulatory usually implies that the patient has come to the location and is not assigned to a bed. Sometimes referred to as an outpatient encounter.</td><td/></tr></table></li><li>Include these codes as defined in <code>urn:undefined</code><table class="none"><tr><td style="white-space:nowrap"><b>Code</b></td><td><b>Display</b></td><td><b><a href="ConceptMap-CMVFencounterClass.html">VF_encounterClass</a></b></td></tr><tr><td>1</td><td>IN</td><td><span title="EQUIVALENT">~</span><a href="http://terminology.hl7.org/5.3.0/CodeSystem-v3-ActCode.html#v3-ActCode-IMP">IMP</a></td></tr><tr><td>0</td><td>OUT</td><td><span title="SOURCEISNARROWERTHANTARGET">&lt;</span><a href="http://terminology.hl7.org/5.3.0/CodeSystem-v3-ActCode.html#v3-ActCode-AMB">AMB</a></td></tr></table></li></ul></div>
  </text>
